  "status": "Draft",
  "summary": "This standard introduces a subclass of tokens known as **PermaLink Asset Bound Tokens (PermaLink-ABTs)**. They are a specific implementation of the broader **Asset Bound Token (ABT)** concept. ABTs establish a novel ownership paradigm where **an asset can own another asset**, enabling composable, nested, and portfolio-like token structures that evolve together over time. PermaLink-ABTs implement a permanent binding mechanism where a token in one smart contract is irreversibly linked to a token in another contract. These links mirror key state data such as `ownerOf`, `tokenId`, `totalSupply`, and `balanceOf` using the `assetBoundContract` interface. Traditional token transfer and approval functions are omitted to enforce immutability and structural cohesion between bound assets. Instead of",
  "title": "PermaLink Asset Bound Token"
